    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends titles XVIII (Medicare) and XIX (Medicaid) of the Social Security Act to add standards for drug compendia&nbsp;used by physicians with respect to&nbsp;payment for certain drugs under the Medicare and Medicaid programs. </p> <p>Specifically, such compendia shall include compendia that, as determined by the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services: (1) are used by health care providers and&nbsp;utilized nationwide by the health insurance industry, (2) have a publicly available policy on disclosures of conflicts of interest,&nbsp; and (3) are accepted by at least one state board of pharmacy or equivalent licensing body.</p>]]></text>
